com.bluegosling.concurrent

Interface Cancellable

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    ListenableFuture<T>, ListenableRepeatingFuture<T>, ListenableScheduledFuture<T>, RepeatingScheduledTask<V>, RunnableListenableFuture<T>, ScheduledTask<V>, ScheduledTaskDefinition<V>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractListenableFuture, ListenableFutureTask, ListenableRepeatingFutureTask, ListenableScheduledFutureTask, SettableFuture, SettableRunnableFuture
    Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.

    @FunctionalInterface
public interface Cancellable
    Represents an activity that can be cancelled. The activity may be in the future or may be a concurrently executing activity.

    • Method Detail

      • cancel

        boolean cancel(boolean mayInterrupt)
        Cancels the activity.
        Parameters:
        mayInterrupt - if true and the activity is executing concurrently, the thread executing the activity may be interrupted
        Returns:
        true if the activity was cancelled; false if it could not be cancelled because the activity has already completed
